<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Kernel on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/kernel/</link><description>Recent content in Kernel on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/kernel/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno 38 ENOSYS — Function not implemented</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-38/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-38/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-38-enosys--function-not-implemented"&gt;[Solution] C errno 38 ENOSYS — Function not implemented&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Function not implemented occurs when a system call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to 38. This error indicates that the requested operation cannot be performed due to the specific condition described by ENOSYS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling a system call that is not supported by the kernel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using features not compiled into the kernel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attempting to use a syscall on an older kernel version.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trying to use a feature on a minimal or embedded system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;sys/mman.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;errno.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;string.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;ptr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;mmap&lt;/span&gt;(NULL, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4096&lt;/span&gt;, PROT_READ, MAP_PRIVATE &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; MAP_ANONYMOUS &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; MAP_POPULATE, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ptr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; MAP_FAILED) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fprintf&lt;/span&gt;(stderr, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;mmap failed: %s (errno %d)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strerror&lt;/span&gt;(errno), errno);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;unistd.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;sys/syscall.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; ret &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;syscall&lt;/span&gt;(SYS_gettid);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ret &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; errno &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; ENOSYS) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fprintf&lt;/span&gt;(stderr, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;gettid syscall not implemented&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-13/"&gt;errno-13 EACCES&lt;/a&gt; — permission denied.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-38/"&gt;errno-38 ENOSYS&lt;/a&gt; — function not implemented (self).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-12/"&gt;errno-12 ENOMEM&lt;/a&gt; — cannot allocate memory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux ENOSYS (errno 38) — Function Not Implemented Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-38/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-38/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-enosys-errno-38--function-not-implemented"&gt;Linux ENOSYS (errno 38) — Function Not Implemented&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENOSYS (errno 38) means the requested system call is not implemented by the kernel. This error occurs when a program tries to use a system call that does not exist on the current kernel version or platform. It is distinct from EINVAL (errno 22) because ENOSYS indicates the syscall itself is missing, not that the arguments are wrong.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running a program compiled for a newer kernel on an older kernel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using system calls not available on the current CPU architecture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The kernel was compiled without support for certain features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Container or chroot environment limiting available syscalls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-enosys"&gt;How to Fix ENOSYS&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-kernel-version"&gt;1. Check Kernel Version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify the running kernel version:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux ENOSYS (errno 63) — Function Not Implemented Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-63/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-63/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-enosys-errno-63--function-not-implemented"&gt;Linux ENOSYS (errno 63) — Function Not Implemented&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENOSYS (errno 63) means the function is not implemented in the kernel. This error occurs when a STREAMS-based or legacy system call is invoked but the kernel does not provide an implementation. It is distinct from EOPNOTSUPP (errno 95) because ENOSYS indicates the function is completely missing, not just unsupported for a specific object.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legacy STREAMS-based system calls not implemented in Linux&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using a function from a different UNIX variant on Linux&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kernel compiled without support for a specific feature&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Container or chroot environment limiting available functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-enosys"&gt;How to Fix ENOSYS&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-kernel-version"&gt;1. Check Kernel Version&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify the running kernel version:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux Kernel Panic — Not Syncing Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/kernel-panic2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/kernel-panic2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-kernel-panic---not-syncing"&gt;Linux: Kernel panic - not syncing&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;Kernel panic - not syncing&lt;/code&gt; is a fatal, unrecoverable error in the Linux kernel. When the kernel encounters a critical error from which it cannot safely continue (such as a corrupted filesystem, missing root filesystem, driver bug, or hardware failure), it halts all operations and displays this message. The system must be rebooted, and the underlying cause must be fixed to prevent recurrence.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] ORA-00600: Internal Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-00600/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-00600/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ora-00600-internal-error"&gt;ORA-00600: Internal Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ORA-00600 is an Oracle internal error that indicates a bug in the Oracle kernel code. It is raised when the database encounters an unexpected internal condition that it cannot handle gracefully.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A known Oracle bug triggered by specific data patterns or operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data corruption in tablespaces or data blocks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient resources (memory, file descriptors) causing internal failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running an Oracle version with known ORA-00600 defects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-the-trace-file"&gt;Check the Trace File&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Trace files are in the dump directory&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -lt $ORACLE_BASE/diag/rdbms/&amp;lt;db_name&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;instance&amp;gt;/trace/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Look for files with &amp;#34;ora&amp;#34; in the name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="search-for-the-first-argument"&gt;Search for the First Argument&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# The error format is: ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [arg1], [arg2], ...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Search Metalink/My Oracle Support for the first argument&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# e.g., ORA-00600: [kcbz_check_objd_typ_3]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="apply-latest-patch-set"&gt;Apply Latest Patch Set&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check current version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;SELECT * FROM v$version;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Download and apply latest CPU/PSU from Oracle Support&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-for-block-corruption"&gt;Check for Block Corruption&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Run RMAN block check
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;BACKUP VALIDATE &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CHECK&lt;/span&gt; LOGICAL &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DATABASE&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Check specific tablespace
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; v$database_block_corruption;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="try-to-open-database-in-restricted-mode"&gt;Try to Open Database in Restricted Mode&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- If database won&amp;#39;t open
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;STARTUP MOUNT;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DATABASE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;OPEN&lt;/span&gt; RESTRICTED;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Internal error during query
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; large_table &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; id &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;123&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [kdsgrp1], [], [], [], [], [], [], []
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Fix: check for block corruption with RMAN
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Error during DDL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; TABLESPACE users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ADD&lt;/span&gt; DATAFILE;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [4194], [30], [25], [], []
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Fix: apply latest patch set
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-01555/"&gt;ORA-01555&lt;/a&gt; — snapshot too old&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-04031/"&gt;ORA-04031&lt;/a&gt; — shared memory allocation failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>